Instructions

1. This plugin uses the data that the TVDB Plugin fetches and enhances it by adding absolute numbering for Anime in Emby
In your anime library (or any library that you want to have absolute numbering), edit the library settings. To get to the settings, go in the admin page, under Server, click on Library and in the library that you want, click the 3 dots and select "edit"

2. Under "Series Metadata Downloader, check "Add Anime Absolute Numbering" and move it on the top. Ensure that TheTVDB is also checked

3. Under "Episode Metadata Downloader, check "Add Anime Absolute Numbering" and move it on the top. Ensure that TheTVDB is also checked

4. Because of the way this plugin works, you may need to scan your library twice.
The first scan will attempt to add the absolute number, but it will not succeed as there is no tvdb info. Checking the TVDB plugin will ensure that it goes and fetches the tvdb info. In the second scan then this plugin picks up the info that the tvdb plugin fetched, and adds the absolute numbering from it.
And voila! You get to see the Season grouping, Episode Number in the season as well as the absolute number in the series
